FBIS3-52717 "drnes005_j_94002" FBIS-NES-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Tribesmen Kidnap U.S. Oil Company Workers NC0701090894 Paris AFP in English 0805 GMT 7 Jan 94 NC0701090894 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Sanaa, Jan 7 (AFP)--Yemeni tribesmen have kidnapped a Canadian, Briton and four Yemenis working for the US firm Hunt Oil, company engineers said Friday. A group from the Daham tribe prevented the six from taking off in their helicopter Tuesday after they inspected a pumping station in the Ma'rib region 100 kilometres (60 miles) east of here. The Yemeni authorities were trying to negotiate the release of the helicopter pilot and five engineers, informed sources said in Sanaa.
